# CGraph — Incomplete Features & Implementation Priorities

> Comprehensive inventory of every stub, placeholder, missing integration, and half-finished feature across the codebase. Prioritized for completion, not deletion.
>
> **Last updated:** 2026-02-17 — 13 of 20 items resolved or implemented

---

## Priority Legend

| Priority | Meaning | Impact |
|----------|---------|--------|
| **P0** | Blocks deployment or core functionality | Must complete before launch |
| **P1** | Major feature gap visible to users | Required for v1.0 |
| **P2** | Noticeable but non-blocking | Target for v1.1 |
| **P3** | Nice-to-have, polish item | Post-launch |

---

## 🔴 P0 — Blocks Core Functionality

### 1. Stripe Payment Integration (Premium Subscriptions) ✅ IMPLEMENTED

**Status:** ~~Placeholder~~ → Real `Stripe.Checkout.Session.create` call wired up (2026-02-17)

| File | Change |
|------|--------|
| [premium_controller.ex](file:///CGraph/apps/backend/lib/cgraph_web/controllers/premium_controller.ex#L214-L255) | `create_checkout_session` now calls `Stripe.Checkout.Session.create` with proper params, success/cancel URLs, and metadata. Returns `checkout_url` for frontend redirect. |
| [stripe_webhook_controller.ex](file:///CGraph/apps/backend/lib/cgraph_web/controllers/stripe_webhook_controller.ex) | Already fully implemented (handles subscription.created/updated/deleted, invoice events) |
| [BillingSettingsPanel.tsx](file:///CGraph/apps/web/src/modules/settings/components/panels/BillingSettingsPanel.tsx#L20-L23) | Already handles `checkout_url` redirect correctly |

**Remaining:** Set `STRIPE_SECRET_KEY`, `STRIPE_PREMIUM_PRICE_ID`, `STRIPE_PREMIUM_PLUS_PRICE_ID`, `STRIPE_WEBHOOK_SECRET` env vars in production.

---

### 2. Group Ban System (Schema + Logic Missing) ✅ IMPLEMENTED

**Status:** ~~Stubs~~ → Full implementation with migration, schema, and CRUD (2026-02-17)

| File | Change |
|------|--------|
| [20260217000001_create_group_bans.exs](file:///CGraph/apps/backend/priv/repo/migrations/20260217000001_create_group_bans.exs) | NEW: Migration creates `group_bans` table with user_id, group_id, reason, banned_by_id, expires_at |
| [group_ban.ex](file:///CGraph/apps/backend/lib/cgraph/groups/group_ban.ex) | NEW: Ecto schema with changeset validation and `active?/1` helper |
| [members.ex](file:///CGraph/apps/backend/lib/cgraph/groups/members.ex) | `ban_member/3,4` creates ban record + removes membership in transaction. `unban_user` deletes ban record. `list_bans` queries active bans with preloads. `get_ban` looks up specific ban. Added `banned?/2` helper. |

---

### 3. Webhooks Persistence (In-Memory Only) 🔶 DEFERRED

**Status:** Still in-memory GenServer. Requires significant refactor to Ecto + Oban.

| File | What's Missing |
|------|---------------|
| [webhooks.ex](file:///CGraph/apps/backend/lib/cgraph/webhooks.ex) | No database persistence for endpoints, deliveries, or retry queue |

**Why deferred:** This is a 500+ line refactor requiring `webhook_endpoints` and `webhook_deliveries` tables, Oban worker integration, and GenServer state migration. Planned for v1.1.

---

### 4. Voice/Video Channels (Schema Only, No Backend) 🔶 DEFERRED

**Status:** Requires external WebRTC infrastructure (LiveKit/Janus/Mediasoup).

**Why deferred:** Cannot be implemented without choosing and deploying a WebRTC SFU. Schema supports voice/stage types but backend signaling requires infrastructure decisions beyond code changes.

---

## 🟠 P1 — Major Feature Gaps

### 5. Marketplace (95% Stubs) ✅ IMPLEMENTED

**Status:** ~~All stubs~~ → Fully wired to `CGraph.Gamification.Marketplace` + real Ecto queries (2026-02-17)

| File | Change |
|------|--------|
| [marketplace.ex](file:///CGraph/apps/backend/lib/cgraph/marketplace.ex) | `browse_listings` queries `marketplace_items` with filters (type, price range, sort). `get_price_history` queries sold items. `create_listing/2` delegates to `GMarketplace`. `create_offer` looks up listing then delegates. `count_active_listings` uses `Repo.aggregate`. `volume_24h` sums sold prices. `trending_items` groups by type with counts. `recent_sales` queries sold items. `featured_listings` sorts by rarity. `user_listings` filters by seller_id. `pending_notifications` returns recent purchases. |

---

### 6. Email Digest Worker (3 Placeholder Functions) ✅ IMPLEMENTED

**Status:** ~~Placeholders~~ → Real Ecto queries against `xp_transactions` and `user_achievements` tables (2026-02-17)

| File | Change |
|------|--------|
| [email_digest_worker.ex](file:///CGraph/apps/backend/lib/cgraph/workers/email_digest_worker.ex) | `calculate_xp_earned` now sums `xp_transactions.amount` for the period. `count_new_achievements` counts `user_achievements` where `unlocked=true` and `unlocked_at >= since`. `fetch_new_achievements` joins with `achievements` table, returns title, description, icon, rarity, xp_reward, unlocked_at. |

---

### 7. Forum Moderation Queue (Always Empty) ✅ IMPLEMENTED

**Status:** ~~Empty stub~~ → Full reporting system with migration, schema, and CRUD (2026-02-17)

| File | Change |
|------|--------|
| [20260217000004_create_content_reports.exs](file:///CGraph/apps/backend/priv/repo/migrations/20260217000004_create_content_reports.exs) | NEW: Migration creates `content_reports` table with reporter, forum, target (polymorphic), reason, status, reviewer fields |
| [content_report.ex](file:///CGraph/apps/backend/lib/cgraph/forums/content_report.ex) | NEW: Schema with changeset + review_changeset. Supports reasons: spam, harassment, hate_speech, misinformation, nsfw, other. Targets: post, comment, user. |
| [core.ex](file:///CGraph/apps/backend/lib/cgraph/forums/core.ex) | `get_mod_queue` now queries pending `ContentReport` records with pagination. Added `report_content/6` to create reports and `review_report/4` to resolve/dismiss. |

